    createStaticVNode('<h1 id="quickstart" tabindex="-1">Quickstart <a class="header-anchor" href="#quickstart" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Quickstart&quot;">​</a></h1><p>This quickstart is for teams that want to launch Gate with the smallest possible amount of reading and the highest possible amount of reusable code.</p><h2 id="what-you-get-from-this-guide" tabindex="-1">What you get from this guide <a class="header-anchor" href="#what-you-get-from-this-guide" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;What you get from this guide&quot;">​</a></h2><p>After completing this guide, you will have:</p><ul><li>a signed server-to-server payment request</li><li>a synchronous API response from Gate</li><li>a callback endpoint that receives the final payment result</li></ul><h2 id="before-you-start" tabindex="-1">Before you start <a class="header-anchor" href="#before-you-start" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Before you start&quot;">​</a></h2><p>Prepare the following:</p><ul><li><code>project_id</code> for your test project</li><li><code>secret_key</code> for signing requests and validating callbacks</li><li>the Gate base URL for your environment</li><li>a callback URL available to the platform</li><li>a test checkout page or API endpoint in your web service</li></ul><h2 id="where-project-id-and-secret-key-come-from" tabindex="-1">Where <code>project_id</code> and <code>secret_key</code> come from <a class="header-anchor" href="#where-project-id-and-secret-key-come-from" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Where `project_id` and `secret_key` come from&quot;">​</a></h2><p>For the first integration, these values are not generated by your code.</p><ul><li><code>project_id</code> is the identifier of the merchant project assigned by Platform during onboarding.</li><li><code>secret_key</code> is the signing key issued for the same project and environment.</li></ul><p>If you do not have them yet, the next action is simple: ask your Platform account manager or technical support to provision a test project and share the test <code>project_id</code> and <code>secret_key</code> for API integration.</p><h2 id="if-you-only-need-the-first-request" tabindex="-1">If you only need the first request <a class="header-anchor" href="#if-you-only-need-the-first-request" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;If you only need the first request&quot;">​</a></h2><p>Go straight to <a href="./gate-quickstart-basic-implementation.html"><strong>Basic implementation</strong></a>. That page shows:</p><ul><li>the exact Gate URL</li><li>the exact JSON payload shape</li><li>how to generate the signature</li><li>how to accept the callback</li></ul><h2 id="best-path-for-first-integration" tabindex="-1">Best path for first integration <a class="header-anchor" href="#best-path-for-first-integration" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Best path for first integration&quot;">​</a></h2><ol><li>Read <a href="./gate-how-to-integrate.html"><strong>Integration overview</strong></a> if you need the architecture in one page.</li><li>Go straight to <a href="./gate-quickstart-basic-implementation.html"><strong>Basic implementation</strong></a> for copy-paste code.</li><li>After the first successful request, continue with <a href="./gate-purchase.html"><strong>One-time purchases</strong></a>, <a href="./gate-requests-format.html"><strong>Request format</strong></a>, and <a href="./signature-gate.html"><strong>Signature generation</strong></a>.</li></ol><h2 id="recommended-implementation-style" tabindex="-1">Recommended implementation style <a class="header-anchor" href="#recommended-implementation-style" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Recommended implementation style&quot;">​</a></h2><p>For a first launch, use the shortest possible path:</p><ul><li>build and sign the final JSON payload on the server side</li><li>send a one-step purchase request to Gate</li><li>treat callbacks as the source of truth for payment status</li></ul><p>Once that works, add two-step flows, refunds, payouts, 3-D Secure handling, and any other payment-specific procedures.</p>', 21)
